          <msContents>
            <summary>Astrological treatise in 102 verses, regarding the calculation of days (tithi) in relation to the moon's rotation (synodic month). Elsewhere attributed to the 17th-century Gujarati author Nageśa.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Nirṇayatattva</title>
              <title type="vernacular">निर्णयतत्त्व</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti nirṇayatattvaṃsamāptaṃ // kālayuktasaṃvatsare phālgunapratipadiguruvāsare vale iti yupanābhnārudhunāthe nalikhitaṃ // cha // cha // cha // śake 1720 (f. 12r) bhādre māsy aite pakṣe bhānaucaikare sthitaḥ pāte kuje ca rohiṇyāṃsaṣaṣṭī kapilāsmṛtā // divaivayogaḥ śastoyaṃ sūryaparvaśatādhikaḥ / yogasyādhadicedrātraucaṃdra ṣaṣṭhIti socyate // 1 // iti nirṇayatatvasamāptaṃ // iti nirṇayatatvasamāptaṃ // // // pakṣadvaye pitithayastithiṃ pūrvāmathottarāṃ // tribhimuhūrtair vidhyaṃ tisāmānyoyaṃvidhiḥ smṛtaḥ // 1 // iti pauṭhīnasiḥ // (f. 12v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
